				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">tepples, excellent point about meta-information. This was partly one reason I suggested an embedded NSF header, so that an embedded player could use the init/play addresses from it. 
<br />
<br />thefox, point taken about the header format, so it will not be in NSF format then. Let's try to allow separation of concerns between the information a player needs to play the music, and the meta-information (track length, name, etc.), so that we can focus on the information the player needs, that is, that which if not present would prevent playing it.
<br />
<br />For the required NES features, I realized that the default should be that an iNES music file requires a fully-accurate NES. Then we have flags that specify that it will work with lesser systems, for example a PPU that only supports $2000 bit 7, or $2002 bit 7.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

