						<div class="postbody">Have you guys seen the player code for the NESM spec? The code was converted by Chris Covell and in turn I converted to ASM6 here recently. You can take any NSF and use the tune switching code with it. It's mapper 0 and only has enough graphics in it to display the number of the tune. You change tunes by pressing the start button.
<br />
<br />I don't know about RAW PCM working in this player, but I suppose it's possible since it's not strictly a NSF anymore.
<br />
<br />I happen to use this quite often.</div>

